{# DEV SAMPLE — render-verbatim copy from handoff/tiers/t-bofu.html; compares the converted layout against the Design render. #}

<section class="section section--compact section--tier-bofu" id="file-review-tldr">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="tldr">
      <p class="tldr__label">TL;DR</p>
      <p class="tldr__body" id="file-review-tldr-body">Send accountant access; in three business days you get a written list of what's wrong, what it costs to fix, and whether the file is fine as-is. Free either way, yours either way.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="file-review-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">What is a QuickBooks file review?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">A certified ProAdvisor reads your file, documents what's broken, and gives you a written fixed-fee scope to repair it.</p></div>
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">What does the review cost?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">Nothing. The review is free, and the written scope is yours either way.</p></div>
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">How long does it take?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">Three business days from the moment we receive accountant access.</p></div>
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">What do you need from me?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">Accountant-level access to QuickBooks — read-only, revocable, no payroll or banking credentials.</p></div>
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">Is my data safe?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">Access is read-only and revocable by you at any time; we never export your file.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="file-review-checks">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <p class="section__eyebrow">What we check</p>
    <h2 class="section__heading">Six passes, every file.</h2>
    <ol class="checks-list" style="margin-top:var(--space-5)">
      <li><span class="num">01</span>Bank and credit-card reconciliation status, every account</li>
      <li><span class="num">02</span>Undeposited funds and suspense balances</li>
      <li><span class="num">03</span>A/R and A/P aging against reality</li>
      <li><span class="num">04</span>Chart of accounts structure and misclassification patterns</li>
      <li><span class="num">05</span>Payroll and sales-tax liability accuracy</li>
      <li><span class="num">06</span>Close discipline — locked periods, audit trail, user access</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="file-review-trust">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="grid-2" style="align-items:start">
      <div class="trust-row" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:var(--space-5)">
        <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">4× ProAdvisor certifications</p><p class="trust-row__label">Online, Payroll, Desktop, Enterprise</p></div>
        <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">Read-only access</p><p class="trust-row__label">Revocable by you, any time</p></div>
        <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">Three business days</p><p class="trust-row__label">From access to written scope</p></div>
      </div>
      <article class="review-card">
        <blockquote class="review-card__quote">"They found eleven months of unreconciled transactions our previous bookkeeper had marked as cleared."</blockquote>
        <div class="review-card__byline">
          <div><span class="review-card__name">M. R— <span style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:10px;color:var(--color-critical)">PLACEHOLDER</span></span><br><span class="review-card__role">Owner, ecommerce · via Clutch</span></div>
          <span class="review-card__verified"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M20 6 9 17l-5-5"></path></svg>Verified</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="file-review-form">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <p class="section__eyebrow">Start now</p>
    <h2 class="section__heading">Request the review.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:var(--fs-13);color:var(--text-secondary)">Condensed render — the full 24-key contract form (all states) is the "intake form" card.</p>
    <form class="intake-form" action="#" method="post" style="margin-top:var(--space-5)">
      <div class="intake-grid">
        <div class="intake-field"><label class="intake-field__label" for="fr-name">Name</label><input id="fr-name" name="name" type="text" required></div>
        <div class="intake-field"><label class="intake-field__label" for="fr-company">Company</label><input id="fr-company" name="company" type="text" required></div>
        <div class="intake-field"><label class="intake-field__label" for="fr-email">Email</label><input id="fr-email" name="email" type="email" required></div>
        <div class="intake-field"><label class="intake-field__label" for="fr-qb">QuickBooks status</label><select id="fr-qb" name="qb_status"><option>QuickBooks Online</option><option>QuickBooks Desktop</option><option>Other software</option></select></div>
      </div>
      <div class="intake-consent"><label class="intake-checkbox"><input type="checkbox" name="consent" value="agreed" required><span>I agree to be contacted about my inquiry.</span></label></div>
      <input type="hidden" name="intent" data-meta="intent" value="file-review"><input type="hidden" name="source_type" data-meta="source_type" value="bofu-conversion"><input type="hidden" name="funnel_stage" data-meta="funnel_stage" value="BOFU">
      <div><button class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" type="submit">Start the File Review</button>
      <p class="intake-form__reassurance">No spam, no list, no obligation. A ProAdvisor replies within one business day.</p></div>
    </form>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="file-review-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header style="margin-bottom:var(--space-6)"><p class="section__eyebrow">Before you send access</p><h2 class="section__heading">The questions buyers actually ask.</h2></header>
    <div class="faq__list" data-faq>
      <div class="faq__item"><h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="ff1">What if the review uncovers more problems than I expected?</button></h3><div class="faq__answer" id="ff1" data-open="false"><p>The scope lists every problem with its own price — you choose what gets fixed and when.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="ff2">Will I get pressured to buy monthly bookkeeping?</button></h3><div class="faq__answer" id="ff2" data-open="false"><p>No. Most reviews end with a one-time fix scope. Monthly service is offered only when the file warrants it.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="ff3">Can I talk to a ProAdvisor first?</button></h3><div class="faq__answer" id="ff3" data-open="false"><p>Yes — call (555) 555-0143 and you'll get an operator, not a sales team.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="ff4">Multi-entity or multi-year — does the free review still apply?</button></h3><div class="faq__answer" id="ff4" data-open="false"><p>Yes. Complex situations take the same three days for the primary file; additional entities are scoped in the same document.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="ff5">Who actually reviews the file?</button></h3><div class="faq__answer" id="ff5" data-open="false"><p>A named, certified ProAdvisor — the same person who would run the engagement if you proceed.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="ff6">What happens if you tell me the file is fine?</button></h3><div class="faq__answer" id="ff6" data-open="false"><p>Then you'll have it in writing — and a shorter worry list. It happens more often than you'd think.</p></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
